 882:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/pbuf.c **** /**
 883:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/pbuf.c ****  * @ingroup pbuf
 884:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/pbuf.c ****  * Chain two pbufs (or pbuf chains) together.
 885:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/pbuf.c ****  *
 886:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/pbuf.c ****  * The caller MUST call pbuf_free(t) once it has stopped
 887:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/pbuf.c ****  * using it. Use pbuf_cat() instead if you no longer use t.
 888:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/pbuf.c ****  *
 889:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/pbuf.c ****  * @param h head pbuf (chain)
 890:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/pbuf.c ****  * @param t tail pbuf (chain)
 891:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/pbuf.c ****  * @note The pbufs MUST belong to the same packet.
 892:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/pbuf.c ****  * @note MAY NOT be called on a packet queue.
